HEADWORD: Hydrocele
<hw>Hy`dro*cele</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/;
<grk>"y`dwr</grk> water + <?/ tumor.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
collection of serous fluid in the areolar texture of the scrotum or in
the coverings, especially in the serous sac, investing the testicle or
the spermatic cord; dropsy of the testicle.</def>⟦br⟧
